D e s c r i p t i o n. H e a d (
fig. 1, 1
) yellow, silvery microtrichose. Length: height: width ratio = 1: 1.59: 1.76. Face gently concave as seen in direct lateral view. Frons above lunule with white setulae. Two brown and an additional white frontal and two orbital seta present. Postocular setae and setulae whitish-yellow. Frons rather broad, subquadrate, about as wide as long and 1.6 as wide as eye. Compound eye about 1.6 times as high as long. Gena about 0.55 times length of flagellomere 1. Flagellomere 1 yellowish brown, 1.8 times as long as wide, pointed at apicodorsal angle; arista basally yellow, distal two-thirds black.

